commits.message:
github: codespell: Add 'TE' word

False positive result:

  Run codespell .
  ./src/gwproxy/http1.c:125: TE ==> THE, BE, WE, TO
  Error: Process completed with exit code 65.

Signed-off-by: Ammar Faizi <ammarfaizi2@gnuweeb.org>

github: codespell: Only spellcheck man dir

Too many false positives for C files.

Signed-off-by: Ammar Faizi <ammarfaizi2@gnuweeb.org>

configure: Add '-Wno-format-truncation' flag

Avoid false positive warning where size-limited '*printf' functions
are used as a length counter.

  In file included from /usr/include/stdio.h:980,
                   from src/gwproxy/http1.c:11:
  In function ‘vsnprintf’,
      inlined from ‘gwnet_http_hdr_fields_addf’ at src/gwproxy/http1.c:916:6:
  /usr/include/x86_64-linux-gnu/bits/stdio2.h:68:10: error: null format string [-Werror=format-truncation=]
     68 |   return __builtin___vsnprintf_chk (__s, __n, __USE_FORTIFY_LEVEL - 1,
        |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
     69 |                                     __glibc_objsize (__s), __fmt, __ap);
        |                                     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  cc1: all warnings being treated as errors

This is not very useful warning. Just disable it.

Signed-off-by: Ammar Faizi <ammarfaizi2@gnuweeb.org>

github: Add 'fetch-depth: 0' to codespell target

When pushing more than one commits, it only knows the HEAD commit
because by default it performs 'git clone' with --depth=1:

  Run git checkout 7f2c098590fe;
  error: pathspec '7f2c098590fe' did not match any file(s) known to git

Add 'fetch-depth: 0' to clone the whole repository.

Signed-off-by: Ammar Faizi <ammarfaizi2@gnuweeb.org>

dns_cache: Fix build errors on Android

Compiling gwproxy on Android results in these errors:

  src/gwproxy/dns_cache.c:138:19: error: incomplete definition of type 'const struct sockaddr_in'
    138 |                         memcpy(i4b, &i4->sin_addr, 4);
        |                                      ~~^
  src/gwproxy/dns_cache.c:131:16: note: forward declaration of 'struct sockaddr_in'
    131 |                 const struct sockaddr_in *i4;
        |                              ^
  src/gwproxy/dns_cache.c:145:19: error: incomplete definition of type 'const struct sockaddr_in6'
    145 |                         memcpy(i6b, &i6->sin6_addr, 16);
        |                                      ~~^
  src/gwproxy/dns_cache.c:130:16: note: forward declaration of 'struct sockaddr_in6'
    130 |                 const struct sockaddr_in6 *i6;
        |                              ^
  2 errors generated.
  make: *** [Makefile:123: src/gwproxy/dns_cache.c.o] Error 1
  make: *** Waiting for unfinished jobs....

Include <arpa/inet.h> to fix it.

Fixes: b88e0ff24816 ("gwproxy/dns_cache: Initial DNS cache rework")
Signed-off-by: Alviro Iskandar Setiawan <alviro.iskandar@gnuweeb.org>

syscall: Fix -Wshorten-64-to-32 warning on Android

Compiling gwproxy on Android results in these warnings:

  In file included from src/gwproxy/ev/epoll.c:8:
  In file included from ./src/gwproxy/ev/epoll.h:8:
  In file included from ./src/gwproxy/gwproxy.h:12:
  ./src/gwproxy/syscall.h:440:9: warning: implicit conversion loses integer precision: 'long' to 'pid_t' (aka 'int') [-Wshorten-64-to-32]
    440 |         return syscall(__NR_gettid);
        |         ~~~~~~ ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  In file included from src/gwproxy/gwproxy.c:7:
  In file included from ./src/gwproxy/gwproxy.h:12:
  ./src/gwproxy/syscall.h:440:9: warning: implicit conversion loses integer precision: 'long' to 'pid_t' (aka 'int') [-Wshorten-64-to-32]
    440 |         return syscall(__NR_gettid);
        |         ~~~~~~ ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  In file included from src/gwproxy/log.c:3:
  ./src/gwproxy/syscall.h:440:9: warning: implicit conversion loses integer precision: 'long' to 'pid_t' (aka 'int') [-Wshorten-64-to-32]
    440 |         return syscall(__NR_gettid);
        |         ~~~~~~ ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Fix this by casting the retval to pid_t.

Fixes: 5e7aa01e2958 ("log: Fix missing `gettid()` syscall on older glibc version")
Signed-off-by: Alviro Iskandar Setiawan <alviro.iskandar@gnuweeb.org>

commits.message:
Fix member and bill calculation errors

The AI addressed several TypeScript errors related to member management and bill calculations. This includes fixing type mismatches in `AddUserDialog`, `BulkUserImportDialog`, `CreateMemberDialog`, and `FlatInfoDialog`, resolving duplicate identifier errors for `useState`, and correcting issues with `useForm` and `generateSecurePassword`. Additionally, it fixed errors in `ImportMembersDialog` related to `Json` to `string` conversion and addressed issues in `supabase/client.ts` and `supabase/utils.ts` concerning type instantiation. Finally, it resolved errors in `advanced-bill-calculations.ts` where properties like `due_date`, `amount`, and `bill_number` were not found on the expected types.

issue.title: Fix down sloped round tunnels glitching
issue.body: This fixes down sloped round tunnels glitching as trains go through. For some reason parts of the background sprites are in the foreground sprites, this cuts and pastes those sections in to the background sprites. There's not really any other way to fix this other than editing the sprites, so any custom content will still have the issue unfortunately. This fixes it for all RCT1, RCT2 and ORCT2 edges. For example, here are the original sprites: And this fix: This is similar to the other tunnel sprites, only these down slope ones have this issue. https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/73112f06-3503-4192-8f29-9f21a05e0d8d https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9853bc83-3920-4690-9aea-d96fe09f171f There's still a few pixels glitching on some edge and track combinations, I did the best I could, some tracks aren't really fitting in to the tunnels in the first place and there has to be at least a little bit of the bottom of the tunnel in the front sprite or it doesn't look right for the majority of tracks.

issue.title: [BUG] All Elemental Systemd services are marked executable (`ls -all /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-*-*.service`)

labels.name: kind/bug
labels.description: Issues that are defects reported by users or that we know have reached a real release

labels.name: severity/2
labels.description: Function working but has a major issue w/o workaround (a major incident with significant impact)

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
On first boot of a single node Harvester cluster `journalctl --follow` shows that all elemental systemd services are marked executable and the logs say that they should not.

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Create a single-node Harvester cluster
1. Shell into the instance, `rancher@ipv4`:
    1. jump in as sudo, `sudo su`
    1. watch as the node comes up for the logs `journalctl --follow`

**Expected behavior**
If it is not an error having an elemental systemd .service file being executable, that the logs would not show that message - if it is in error having the elemental .service systemd files being executable, then maybe they shouldn't be.

**Environment**
 - Harvester ISO version:  v1.3-head
 - Underlying Infrastructure: bare-metal / qemu-kvm

**Additional context**
Journalctl Example log:
```log
Jun 03 17:57:38 testnode4-v13head0603 systemd[1]: Configuration file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-initramfs.service is marked executable. Please remove executable permission bits. Proceeding anyway.
Jun 03 17:57:38 testnode4-v13head0603 systemd[1]: Configuration file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-reconcile.timer is marked executable. Please remove executable permission bits. Proceeding anyway.
Jun 03 17:57:38 testnode4-v13head0603 systemd[1]: Configuration file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-reconcile.service is marked executable. Please remove executable permission bits. Proceeding anyway.
Jun 03 17:57:38 testnode4-v13head0603 systemd[1]: Configuration file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-network.service is marked executable. Please remove executable permission bits. Proceeding anyway.
Jun 03 17:57:38 testnode4-v13head0603 systemd[1]: Configuration file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-boot.service is marked executable. Please remove executable permission bits. Proceeding anyway.
Jun 03 17:57:38 testnode4-v13head0603 systemd[1]: Configuration file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-rootfs.service is marked executable. Please remove executable permission bits. Proceeding anyway.
Jun 03 17:57:38 testnode4-v13head0603 systemd[1]: Configuration file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-fs.service is marked executable. Please remove executable permission bits. Proceeding anyway.
```

And additionally after the node is booted fully (Harvester VIP) is accessible, sill noting:
```log
Last login: Mon Jun  3 17:54:04 2024 from 192.168.9.163
rancher@testnode4-v13head0603:~> sudo su
testnode4-v13head0603:/home/rancher # file /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-fs.service 
/usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-fs.service: ASCII text
testnode4-v13head0603:/home/rancher # ls -all /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-fs.service
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 root root 261 May 31 02:29 /usr/lib/systemd/system/elemental-setup-fs.service
testnode4-v13head0603:/home/rancher # 
```

comment.body:
I checked the v1.5.1 and v1.6.0-rc6.
It appears that these services are also executable.

reopen it for tracking
